This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on January 12, 2018, in honor of Martin Luther King, Jr. The proclamation acknowledges Dr. King's dedication to fighting segregation and discrimination and his vision of a nation where all Americans have equal opportunities. It also recognizes the 50th anniversary of Dr. King's assassination and highlights the importance of fulfilling his legacy by working towards justice and equality. The proclamation encourages Americans to observe the Martin Luther King, Jr. Federal Holiday with civic, community, and service programs and activities.